In addition, the overall recalculation of votes in all polling stations will be possible if there is an indication that the difference between the potential winner of the election and the candidate in the second place is less than or equal to one percentage point; whenever an express request from the representative of the party and/or the coalition proposed by the candidate in the second place is made at the beginning of the meeting.
The overall recalculation of votes will also be possible if, after proper counting, it is found that the difference between the likely winner and the candidate in the second place is equal to or less than one percentage point, and also whenever there is an express request from the political party whose candidate has ended in the second place. In such a case, the electoral packages in which partial counting has been carried out will be cut.
