And finally, long-term unemployment is very widespread: 53% for disabled versus 38% on average.
In short, these are criteria that are particularly complicated to return to employment and which are "the core problem", according to Christian Grapina, Director General of the Tremplin Association, which was founded in 1992 to help businesses accept disabled workers.
